\title{Destructor ([C++](OGCS1))}

\p{A destructor is the mechanism in [C++](OGCS1) that ensures that any memory a constructor allocates is deallocated.}
\p{A destructor is a function of a [class](KE3D) that shares the same name as the class with the \code{~} operator to denote it is the \em{complement} of the constructor.}
